The paper studies bidding algorithms in multiple-object auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithms involve permutations, which suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AI). The paper also discusses budgets, which is a common consideration in economic theory and mechanism design (cs.EC). Finally, the paper uses mathematical optimization techniques to derive the optimal bidding algorithm, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
